    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2168478">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2168478">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2168478)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2168478">
																		So, dystopias and stuff.
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dillinger-phd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005876); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2005876&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164745" alt="Dillinger PhD" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2005876)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dillinger-phd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005876); return false;" >Dillinger PhD</a></span> <span class="odate time_1417249729 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Nov 2014 08:28</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2168478">
									

<p>My submission, which I hope y'all enjoy. This one is a lot of things in a small amount of words for me; meditations about life, on the meaning of the standards we carry with us, on our relationship with the concept of death on multiple levels. While most people might be inclined to ask where you were when the world ended, I wanted to think about who you were.</p>
<p>Thanks to Prior, Charon, Agent MacLeod, Reach, and Tagliafierro for taking a look at this one.</p>

							</div>

								
					
						<div class="options">
				
													<strong><a href="javascript:;" onclick="postReply(event,2168478)" class="btn btn-primary btn-small btn-sm">Reply</a></strong> 
