    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2169397">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2169397">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2169397)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2169397">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dillinger-phd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005876); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2005876&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164745" alt="Dillinger PhD" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2005876)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dillinger-phd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005876); return false;" >Dillinger PhD</a></span> <span class="odate time_1417381844 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Nov 2014 21:10</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2169397">
									

<p>I see your points, albeit the concept (as it evolved into, at least) isn't about Earth. I am wanting to explore the idea more in the future but this tale became, for me, about Reichardt. I personally enjoy the idea of the destruction of the planet being marginalized here; it reflects its status within the story at large while being a juxtaposition to Reichardt's feelings on the subject.</p>
<p>The tale could be a little more fleshed out; this was a case where the contest timeline, my late start, and personal schedule conflicts for the last couple days led me to putting this up before I could decide what (if any) additions I felt were necessary. But I really enjoy it as it stands and if there was more going on, very little of it would have addressed the planet; perhaps a little more on the Foundation would have cropped up but most of the words would have been spent on the protagonist and his family.</p>

							</div>

								
					
