		<div class="post" id="post-2174526">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2174526)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2174526">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dillinger-phd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005876); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2005876&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164745" alt="Dillinger PhD" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2005876)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dillinger-phd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005876); return false;" >Dillinger PhD</a></span> <span class="odate time_1418018786 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Dec 2014 06:06</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2174526">
									

<p>I appreciate the comments and the upvote, particularly in light of feeling like this needed work. The longish paragraphs are something of a style thing for me, although I do intend to move away from them a bit more; in my fiction work at large I tend to shy away from heavy dialogue and it can sometimes lead to walloftext-itis. I see how they look especially odd given the length of this work.</p>
<p>As for half-assing the concept, I disagree. The &quot;Earth as SCP&quot; idea was the initial starting point but I decided deliberately to bury the lead, so to speak. A very character-driven tale where the destruction of our homeworld is treated so insignificantly spoke to me really strongly. I do concede that this is a case where I'm not meeting the expectations of readers with the rest of the story that I give them at the beginning; I'm okay with that.</p>
<p>Thanks kindly for the words :)</p>

							</div>

								
					
